
[1]easement

   E'ASEMENT, n. Convenience; accommodation; that which gives ease, relief
   or assistance.

   He has the advantage of a free lodging, and some other easements.

   In law, any privilege or convenience which one man has of another,
   either by prescription or charter,without profit;as a way through his
   land, &c.
